WEBVTT

00:00:11.790 --> 00:00:13.820
Welcome back, Spe-chan.

00:00:16.090 --> 00:00:18.450
You did well in the Kikkashou.

00:00:20.340 --> 00:00:22.200
I lost!

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:25.380
That's too bad.

00:00:31.430 --> 00:00:33.670
You're going to put on weight
if you eat this late.

00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:39.380
I'll start training really hard
again tomorrow. It's okay.

00:00:42.690 --> 00:00:45.380
Seiun Sky-san was pretty amazing out there.

00:00:45.380 --> 00:00:47.480
I couldn't catch up to her at all.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:51.980
I did it!

00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:55.450
I think you can be proud of
coming in second, though.

00:00:55.450 --> 00:00:59.050
But you came in first the other day.

00:00:59.790 --> 00:01:01.480
Do you want any yatsuhashi?

00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:03.180
I already had some.

00:01:03.180 --> 00:01:06.750
Besides, I have a race next week.

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:06.750
{\an8}Tennoushou

00:01:06.750 --> 00:01:09.150
The fall Tennoushou, right?

00:01:10.570 --> 00:01:14.030
I want to run with you at least once.

00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:17.470
What race do you have after that one?

00:01:17.470 --> 00:01:18.300
{\an8}Tennoushou

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:20.730
{\an8}Japan C

00:01:19.170 --> 00:01:20.730
The Japan Cup…

00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:23.470
I wanna run in that, too…

00:01:23.470 --> 00:01:26.190
You'll have to ask Trainer-san.

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:29.770
But I want to try running with you, too.

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:32.330
What? Really?

00:01:32.330 --> 00:01:34.780
Then how about we both go ask him?

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:39.190
Yeah, we might not get
another chance anytime soon.

00:01:39.190 --> 00:01:40.780
Wh-Why's that?

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:46.540
I'm thinking of going to
America after the Japan Cup.

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:47.530
What?

00:01:48.580 --> 00:01:50.040
What?!

00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:53.410
So we should run together,
no matter what.

00:01:53.410 --> 00:01:55.050
It's a promise.

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:05.990
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:02:05.990 --> 00:02:12.520
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:14.570 --> 00:02:20.870
{\an8}Umamusume

00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:20.740
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:28.470
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:02:28.470 --> 00:02:33.490
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:02:33.490 --> 00:02:39.100
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:02:39.100 --> 00:02:45.960
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:02:46.770 --> 00:02:51.960
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:59.240
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:04.660
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:03:04.660 --> 00:03:10.130
I want to see that shining future with you

00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:15.640
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:23.400
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:03:25.010 --> 00:03:29.020
{\an8}Race 7

00:03:25.010 --> 00:03:29.020
{\an8}Promise

00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:32.020
You're all here, right?

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:34.520
The finish line will be over there.

00:03:35.050 --> 00:03:36.730
The finish line…

00:03:36.730 --> 00:03:37.210
Fuchu

00:03:36.730 --> 00:03:38.970
{\an8}Where is this?

00:03:37.210 --> 00:03:39.990
{\an9}Inn

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:39.990
An inn?

00:03:39.990 --> 00:03:42.260
That's pretty deep in the mountains.

00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:43.990
How long is this going to take?

00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:45.300
It'll help you train for hills,

00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:50.040
{\an8}Defeat Team Rigil!

00:03:45.300 --> 00:03:46.700
and give you more stamina.

00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:48.340
We're going to get through those fall G-I's.

00:03:48.340 --> 00:03:50.740
And someone here lost the Kikkashou, right?

00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:53.130
Yes, that was me.

00:03:53.130 --> 00:03:54.380
Yep, that was you.

00:03:54.380 --> 00:03:55.980
It's 3:00 PM right now.

00:03:54.380 --> 00:03:59.260
{\an8}Defeat Team Rigil!

00:03:55.980 --> 00:03:58.940
You don't get any dinner unless
you make it there by 6 PM.

00:03:58.940 --> 00:03:59.940
What?!

00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:01.440
Anyway, good luck.

00:04:01.440 --> 00:04:02.720
What?!

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:06.730
Is he really a trainer?

00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:08.350
He's amusing, huh?

00:04:08.670 --> 00:04:11.460
And he wants us to
run an impossible path…

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:14.880
This is more like a spiritual
exercise than training.

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:16.130
Seriously.

00:04:16.130 --> 00:04:16.940
Hey!

00:04:17.410 --> 00:04:19.440
H-Hey, Suzuka-senpai!

00:04:19.850 --> 00:04:23.650
Who gave Suzuka-san the map?!

00:04:23.650 --> 00:04:26.240
We're going to get lost!

00:04:27.630 --> 00:04:29.540
Wait!

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:35.790
Opera O, you're not moving your arms enough!

00:04:36.180 --> 00:04:36.950
Right!

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:39.630
{\an9}T. M. Opera O

00:04:39.630 --> 00:04:42.100
We can't keep losing to Spica!

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:44.780
We have the most victories overall this year!
We need to show people our pride!

00:04:44.780 --> 00:04:46.140
There we go…

00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:47.340
Maruzensky-san…

00:04:47.810 --> 00:04:48.970
What's up?

00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:53.430
Could you run with me?

00:04:53.950 --> 00:04:56.940
I guess you really wanted
to win the Mainichi Okan.

00:04:57.530 --> 00:04:59.190
It was the first time I lost.

00:04:59.650 --> 00:05:02.400
I don't want to get used to that feeling.

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:03.650
All right.

00:05:03.650 --> 00:05:05.640
My leg has completely recovered.

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:07.510
Please help me.

00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:09.160
No problem. Leave it to me.

00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.870
Let's see if you can keep up with me.

00:05:13.430 --> 00:05:15.130
Thank you so much.

00:05:15.130 --> 00:05:16.060
Let's go.

00:05:16.060 --> 00:05:17.330
Right.

00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:21.150
The two of you are going to be in
the Tennoushou this fall, right?

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:26.990
Air Groove-senpai, you beat Suzuka-san
in the fall Tennoushou last year, right?

00:05:26.990 --> 00:05:30.720
Yes, I won then, but I lost
this year's Takarazuka Kinen.

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:35.100
Suzuka's completely different
than she was last year.

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:37.670
What are you so afraid of?

00:05:37.670 --> 00:05:40.890
I'm going to beat Suzuka hands down.

00:05:40.890 --> 00:05:41.820
That's the spirit.

00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:44.040
But don't let your guard down.

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:47.450
Suzuka has changed since she left Rigil.

00:05:47.970 --> 00:05:49.320
How is she different now?

00:05:49.900 --> 00:05:54.240
A typical race is about strategy and tactics.
You're trying to beat the other horse girls.

00:05:54.990 --> 00:05:57.740
But now, Suzuka always gives her all,
no matter the distance,

00:05:57.740 --> 00:05:59.880
as if she was running a time trial.

00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:02.460
She doesn't care about the other horse girls.

00:06:03.570 --> 00:06:05.230
Fine by me.

00:06:05.650 --> 00:06:07.550
Then I'll go head to head with her.

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:10.810
Senpai, I'm not sure if that's the best idea.

00:06:10.810 --> 00:06:12.500
No, it's not a bad idea.

00:06:12.500 --> 00:06:13.330
Huh?

00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:17.350
Don't count on her to get tired at the
end like you did in the Mainichi Okan.

00:06:17.830 --> 00:06:20.020
You shouldn't wait at the back of the pack.

00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:21.690
You need to give Suzuka a run for her money.

00:06:22.100 --> 00:06:24.680
I'm going to make you proud, Hana-san.

00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:26.850
I'm not going to lose!

00:06:28.400 --> 00:06:30.830
I won't lose anymore, either!

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:33.010
If I keep losing to Suzuka-san,

00:06:33.010 --> 00:06:35.160
I won't be able to proudly go to
the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:36.650
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe?

00:06:37.070 --> 00:06:38.420
That's what you're going after?

00:06:41.090 --> 00:06:42.380
Then win this.

00:06:42.870 --> 00:06:43.650
Right.

00:06:48.030 --> 00:06:49.880
I can't do this…

00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:51.800
Neither can I…

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:54.310
It's so dark. I'm scared!

00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:57.850
That's…

00:06:58.180 --> 00:06:59.380
Our trainer!

00:06:59.850 --> 00:07:00.730
Hey there.

00:07:02.050 --> 00:07:04.360
W-We made it…

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:06.140
I'm so happy to see light again…

00:07:06.140 --> 00:07:07.810
You guys are late.

00:07:07.810 --> 00:07:09.990
Were you seriously taking a bath?!

00:07:10.300 --> 00:07:12.000
Hurry up and go take your baths.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:13.190
Clean off that sweat.

00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:15.360
As if you had to ask!

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:16.450
You guys…

00:07:16.450 --> 00:07:18.350
But before that…

00:07:20.010 --> 00:07:22.460
I'm going to thank you for this…

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:30.470
I-I'm sorry! F-Forgive me!

00:07:32.970 --> 00:07:34.970
{\an8}Be thoughtful in the bath! Please allow
your fellow bathers an enjoyable experience.

00:07:40.350 --> 00:07:41.560
What?!

00:07:43.270 --> 00:07:45.810
But the Japan Cup is almost here!

00:07:46.130 --> 00:07:48.630
So you'll be in America
by the end of the year?

00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:50.150
Yeah, that's the plan.

00:07:50.150 --> 00:07:51.260
No way!

00:07:51.260 --> 00:07:53.660
When are you coming back?

00:07:53.660 --> 00:07:56.280
I haven't decided yet.

00:07:56.670 --> 00:08:00.160
But I plan on staying there
until I feel it's time to leave.

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:05.150
I wanted to keep seeing
you run in person.

00:08:05.150 --> 00:08:08.500
I'm sorry I couldn't really tell you guys.

00:08:08.870 --> 00:08:10.510
It'll be lonely without you.

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:18.570
Please, let me participate in the Japan Cup.

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:19.310
Girls!

00:08:19.690 --> 00:08:20.890
You're eating too much!

00:08:20.890 --> 00:08:23.150
What's up with all this food?

00:08:23.150 --> 00:08:24.780
I heard it was all you can eat.

00:08:24.780 --> 00:08:26.020
It's not!

00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:29.180
Could we get a some premium sushi over here?

00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:29.420
What?!

00:08:29.420 --> 00:08:31.020
I'll have some carrots!

00:08:31.020 --> 00:08:31.360
What?!

00:08:31.360 --> 00:08:32.850
No problem.

00:08:32.850 --> 00:08:34.440
G-Girls…

00:08:34.440 --> 00:08:35.780
Trainer-san!

00:08:37.010 --> 00:08:38.510
So, you were saying?

00:08:38.510 --> 00:08:39.930
The Japan Cup.

00:08:39.930 --> 00:08:42.400
You want to run with Suzuka, right?

00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:42.750
Yes.

00:08:43.950 --> 00:08:46.460
Somebody on our team would
be on the losing end.

00:08:46.460 --> 00:08:48.460
So I'd rather not, but…

00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:50.110
Please!

00:08:50.540 --> 00:08:54.030
You've always been all about Suzuka, huh?

00:08:55.310 --> 00:08:56.800
Fine.

00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:01.050
But if Suzuka loses in the Tennoushou,

00:09:01.050 --> 00:09:02.810
I can't promise you anything
for the Japan Cup.

00:09:03.140 --> 00:09:05.750
And Suzuka came in 6th place last year.

00:09:05.750 --> 00:09:08.060
But with the way she is now,
Suzuka couldn't lose.

00:09:08.060 --> 00:09:09.310
Exactly.

00:09:09.310 --> 00:09:11.230
Really, and you call yourself a trainer?

00:09:12.490 --> 00:09:16.110
You're so lucky, Spe. I wanted
to run with Suzuka, too.

00:09:16.110 --> 00:09:17.450
Me, too.

00:09:17.450 --> 00:09:19.050
Suzuka-senpai,

00:09:19.050 --> 00:09:20.810
you have lots of people
waiting to go up against you,

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:22.670
so make sure you come back home soon.

00:09:22.670 --> 00:09:24.960
Yeah, I look forward to it.

00:09:24.960 --> 00:09:28.670
We'll have to win more, so we
can be in races together.

00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:33.760
I suppose that means I'll be able to run
with Suzuka sooner than you, McQueen.

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:37.260
No, I think it's obvious
I'll run with her first.

00:09:37.260 --> 00:09:37.260
It'll be me!

00:09:37.570 --> 00:09:38.700
No, me!

00:09:38.700 --> 00:09:40.980
It'll be me!

00:09:40.980 --> 00:09:43.220
I'm going to be the one running with Suzuka!

00:09:49.270 --> 00:09:52.790
Two months' salary gone in a flash.

00:09:53.290 --> 00:09:55.650
Spica's a good team.

00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:57.780
Everyone's kind of rough
around the edges, though.

00:09:57.780 --> 00:10:03.790
I can't eat any more…

00:10:04.170 --> 00:10:06.890
You set the atmosphere for me
to tell everyone, didn't you?

00:10:06.890 --> 00:10:09.120
To tell everyone that I'm going to America.

00:10:09.470 --> 00:10:11.670
Well, that was part of it.

00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:15.250
I thought it'd help morale, too.

00:10:15.250 --> 00:10:17.760
We need to show Hana-san what we're made of.

00:10:18.710 --> 00:10:22.210
Thank you for inviting me to join this team.

00:10:22.210 --> 00:10:24.140
Oh? What's with you all of a sudden?

00:10:25.570 --> 00:10:27.630
Fell asleep, huh?

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:35.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

00:10:39.030 --> 00:10:43.030
{\an8}Umamusume

00:10:39.030 --> 00:10:43.030
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:45.540
{\an8}Tennoushou Fall

00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:57.510
{\an8}Tennoushou Fall

00:10:48.580 --> 00:10:50.500
<i>It's November 1st.</i>

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:53.090
<i>It's the 11th race at the Tokyo Racetrack.</i>

00:10:53.090 --> 00:10:56.390
<i>Bracket 1, Number 1 will be
the most popular horse girl,</i>

00:10:56.390 --> 00:10:57.510
<i>Silence Suzuka.</i>

00:10:57.950 --> 00:11:01.660
<i>There are so many 1s appearing today.
It feels kind of like fate.</i>

00:11:02.510 --> 00:11:04.760
<i>All the Suzuka merchandise
has already sold out.</i>

00:11:02.510 --> 00:11:04.760
{\an8}Silence Suzuka
Mascot Plush
Sold Out!!

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:07.020
{\an8}Silence Suzuka
Mug
Sold Out!!

00:11:05.090 --> 00:11:09.270
<i>There are so many people here
today at the Tokyo Racecourse</i>

00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:09.270
{\an8}Silence Suzuka
Strap
Sold Out!!

00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:12.770
<i>to see her run beautifully out there.</i>

00:11:12.770 --> 00:11:15.650
Suzuka-san, hurry up!

00:11:25.020 --> 00:11:26.990
Suzuka, what's wrong?

00:11:26.990 --> 00:11:29.410
I'm just redoing my strap.

00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:30.020
{\an7}Mejiro Ryan

00:11:29.410 --> 00:11:30.780
See you on the track, then.

00:11:30.780 --> 00:11:31.370
Right.

00:11:32.660 --> 00:11:35.170
Let's both do our best out there.

00:11:32.660 --> 00:11:34.850
{\an9}Nice Nature

00:11:35.170 --> 00:11:36.090
Yeah.

00:11:43.850 --> 00:11:45.510
I'm so nervous!

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:46.830
{\an9}Winning Ticket

00:11:45.510 --> 00:11:47.600
I'm itching all over…

00:11:51.770 --> 00:11:54.320
Don't try to get away from me.

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:57.010
G-Good luck out there.

00:12:01.970 --> 00:12:05.160
<i>The last one out is Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:09.580
That's some thunderous
cheering from the crowd.

00:12:09.580 --> 00:12:12.080
You can do it, Suzuka!

00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:12.080
She's really popular!

00:12:15.370 --> 00:12:16.790
Suzuka-san!

00:12:19.570 --> 00:12:20.240
Everyone…

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:21.380
Suzuka-san!

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:25.010
I'll be counting on you to
make some waves out there.

00:12:26.460 --> 00:12:28.410
Please take this.

00:12:27.430 --> 00:12:29.850
{\an8}Good luck!

00:12:30.370 --> 00:12:33.160
This is from when you ran in the Derby…

00:12:33.160 --> 00:12:34.690
I was thinking it might do you some good.

00:12:35.990 --> 00:12:38.420
Yeah, you can count on me.

00:12:38.420 --> 00:12:40.610
Suzuka-san!

00:12:39.470 --> 00:12:40.610
Suzuka!

00:12:43.610 --> 00:12:45.180
I'm going to have some fun out there.

00:12:47.860 --> 00:12:52.500
I imagine the secret to her strength
is her ability to have fun racing.

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:58.750
She always told me to
have fun before my races.

00:13:05.260 --> 00:13:06.890
Suzuka-san…

00:13:08.740 --> 00:13:11.230
I don't lose to the same person twice.

00:13:11.980 --> 00:13:16.390
I'm going to beat you, and proudly try my
hand at the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:13:16.990 --> 00:13:18.650
Let's see if you can keep up with me.

00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:20.520
Oh, I <i>will</i>.

00:13:23.610 --> 00:13:26.530
<i>The twelve horse girls
have entered their gates.</i>

00:13:26.920 --> 00:13:30.130
El Condor Pasa, Hishi Amazon, Winning Ticket,

00:13:30.130 --> 00:13:31.790
Mejiro Ryan, Nice Nature…

00:13:31.790 --> 00:13:35.120
<i>Will they be able to catch Silence Suzuka?</i>

00:13:42.580 --> 00:13:44.590
The gates have opened!

00:13:47.660 --> 00:13:49.300
That's a good start!

00:13:49.300 --> 00:13:52.010
<i>Silence Suzuka has quickly taken
her position at the front!</i>

00:13:52.510 --> 00:13:55.350
<i>El Condor Pasa is in second.</i>

00:13:55.350 --> 00:13:57.940
<i>I'm going to catch up to Suzuka-san.</i>

00:13:57.940 --> 00:13:59.450
That's right, El.

00:13:59.450 --> 00:14:00.650
Keep on her.

00:14:01.390 --> 00:14:03.530
W-Wait, what's going on?

00:14:03.530 --> 00:14:06.700
<i>Silence Suzuka is breaking
further away from the pack.</i>

00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:08.450
<i>That's some impressive speed!</i>

00:14:09.710 --> 00:14:10.950
<i>She's fast!</i>

00:14:13.580 --> 00:14:16.330
<i>She won't even let me go one-on-one with her!</i>

00:14:16.330 --> 00:14:18.210
<i>She's going even faster than I expected.</i>

00:14:18.210 --> 00:14:19.770
<i>She's way too…</i>

00:14:19.770 --> 00:14:21.170
<i>…fast!</i>

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:22.670
<i>Why?!</i>

00:14:22.670 --> 00:14:24.460
<i>We're about to hit the third turn!</i>

00:14:24.460 --> 00:14:26.740
<i>There's a huge gap now!</i>

00:14:34.180 --> 00:14:36.320
<i>Her 1,000 meter time is…</i>

00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:38.270
<i>57.4 seconds!</i>

00:14:38.270 --> 00:14:39.750
57.4?!

00:14:40.300 --> 00:14:41.920
You can't be serious!

00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:43.690
How is she that fast?

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:48.490
Suzuka-san is really amazing!

00:14:50.200 --> 00:14:53.010
Silence Suzuka keeps flying!

00:14:53.010 --> 00:14:56.910
I've never seen a horse
girl run this fast before.

00:14:56.910 --> 00:14:59.590
<i>Just how many horse lengths is she ahead?!</i>

00:14:59.590 --> 00:15:02.670
<i>The cheers here in the stadium
are reaching a fever pitch!</i>

00:15:06.130 --> 00:15:09.340
<i>My energy and stamina are
the best they've ever been.</i>

00:15:09.990 --> 00:15:12.010
<i>I can run even faster.</i>

00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:16.220
She's started running even faster!

00:15:19.130 --> 00:15:20.480
Go!

00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:22.070
Suzuka-san!

00:15:22.070 --> 00:15:23.770
<i>I can keep…</i>

00:15:38.180 --> 00:15:39.120
Huh?

00:15:49.430 --> 00:15:51.030
<i>Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:15:51.030 --> 00:15:52.970
<i>There's something wrong with Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:15:53.790 --> 00:15:55.310
<i>What's going on here?</i>

00:15:55.310 --> 00:15:57.470
<i>There's a problem here.</i>

00:15:57.850 --> 00:16:00.370
<i>Is Silence Suzuka okay?</i>

00:16:00.370 --> 00:16:02.850
<i>Just what happened on the other side
of that big Japanese zelkova tree?</i>

00:16:03.170 --> 00:16:05.730
<i>Everyone's confused here.</i>

00:16:05.730 --> 00:16:08.860
<i>There's something wrong
with Silence Suzuka…</i>

00:16:07.910 --> 00:16:11.110
{\an8}Mejiro Ryan and Nice Nature are
coming in from the outside.

00:16:08.860 --> 00:16:12.860
<i>El Condor Pasa is in the lead.</i>

00:16:11.110 --> 00:16:13.950
{\an8}The race is continuing
into the fourth turn…

00:16:18.120 --> 00:16:20.390
{\an8}Tennoushou (Fall) GI November 1st

00:16:59.910 --> 00:17:02.910
{\an6}Good luck!

00:17:05.410 --> 00:17:06.920
Suzuka-san…

00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:09.340
Where am I?

00:17:09.340 --> 00:17:10.470
Suzuka-san…

00:17:11.070 --> 00:17:13.010
H-Hold on a second!

00:17:13.010 --> 00:17:14.610
I'm going to get Trainer-san!

00:17:25.390 --> 00:17:29.150
{\an6}Good luck!

00:17:29.150 --> 00:17:31.650
{\an3}Good luck!

00:17:32.900 --> 00:17:33.610
Yo.

00:17:33.610 --> 00:17:34.970
Trainer-san…

00:17:35.610 --> 00:17:36.830
Don't push yourself!

00:17:40.730 --> 00:17:42.200
Relax.

00:17:42.200 --> 00:17:43.850
Um, I…

00:17:43.850 --> 00:17:47.270
I'm glad we're able to talk like this.

00:17:48.390 --> 00:17:51.150
What should I say to her?

00:17:51.150 --> 00:17:52.130
A fracture…

00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:55.290
You've been working a pretty hard schedule.

00:17:55.290 --> 00:17:57.090
You'll have to rest for a while.

00:17:57.590 --> 00:18:01.080
If it's just a fracture, it'll heal, right?

00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.430
Yeah, of course.

00:18:04.230 --> 00:18:05.630
I'll be able to run, right?

00:18:06.270 --> 00:18:08.390
Yeah, well…

00:18:10.730 --> 00:18:13.940
Will I be able to race at full speed again?

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:18.300
About that…

00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:25.950
We don't know if you'll be able to run
100 percent like you did before.

00:18:29.470 --> 00:18:31.380
No, you will be able to!

00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:36.030
You'll be able to race again!

00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:40.050
You promised me, didn't you, Suzuka-san?

00:18:40.050 --> 00:18:40.970
Promised you?

00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:49.270
I'll make sure you'll be able to run
at 100 percent! No, 120 percent!

00:18:50.910 --> 00:18:52.110
Spe-chan…

00:18:52.660 --> 00:18:53.970
That Spe…

00:18:53.970 --> 00:18:56.550
I hear that rehabilitation
is really difficult,

00:18:56.550 --> 00:18:58.860
but you'll be fine, I'm sure!

00:18:58.860 --> 00:19:00.500
D-Don't push me!

00:19:02.630 --> 00:19:04.020
G-Girls…

00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:06.120
You guys were listening?

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:08.960
Don't hurt yourselves. This is
a hospital, you know?

00:19:09.870 --> 00:19:11.360
Suzuka!

00:19:11.360 --> 00:19:13.350
I was so worried about you.

00:19:13.350 --> 00:19:16.090
I'm sorry for worrying you, everyone.

00:19:16.090 --> 00:19:17.140
You better be!

00:19:17.140 --> 00:19:18.050
Hey—

00:19:18.050 --> 00:19:21.300
I feel better now that I've seen you.

00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:27.840
Spe-chan kept saying that you had a
fracture and refused to leave your side.

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:30.640
Teio-san, you're supposed
to keep that a secret.

00:19:31.130 --> 00:19:34.970
Suzuka-senpai, I'll draw something
on your cast to wish you well.

00:19:34.970 --> 00:19:38.170
Scarlet, it's a bit early
for your scribbling.

00:19:38.170 --> 00:19:39.750
You should do this before
she gets discharged.

00:19:41.370 --> 00:19:44.150
I am the God of Horse Girls.

00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:46.830
{\an8}God

00:19:44.150 --> 00:19:45.210
What?

00:19:45.210 --> 00:19:50.060
Silence Suzuka, I can see your future.

00:19:50.060 --> 00:19:52.830
God, please tell us her future!

00:19:52.830 --> 00:19:59.300
{\an8}God

00:19:53.170 --> 00:19:54.610
Let's see…

00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:57.190
You're running on green turf.

00:19:57.190 --> 00:19:59.300
I-Is this America?!

00:19:59.300 --> 00:20:01.420
What race in America?

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:02.080
Huh?

00:20:02.080 --> 00:20:03.870
The, uh…

00:20:04.550 --> 00:20:06.000
New York Cup!

00:20:04.550 --> 00:20:07.060
{\an8}God

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.060
That doesn't exist.

00:20:07.420 --> 00:20:08.010
Huh?

00:20:08.010 --> 00:20:08.900
It doesn't?

00:20:08.900 --> 00:20:10.100
It sounds like it should.

00:20:10.100 --> 00:20:12.040
You didn't think this through at all!

00:20:12.040 --> 00:20:14.830
Well, I guess you did an okay job, for you.

00:20:12.040 --> 00:20:16.150
{\an4}God

00:20:14.830 --> 00:20:16.670
Sh-Shut up!

00:20:20.740 --> 00:20:24.990
Suzuka-senpai, do you remember
what happened at the end?

00:20:24.990 --> 00:20:26.740
At the end?

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:31.440
If you fall at top speed, you can die.

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:34.210
Spe-senpai helped you, and so you
only ended up with a fracture.

00:20:34.530 --> 00:20:36.240
I didn't…

00:20:36.240 --> 00:20:38.380
The doctor said she did a good job.

00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:38.980
Yeah.

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:39.550
Huh?

00:20:39.550 --> 00:20:42.270
She was amazing.

00:20:43.460 --> 00:20:44.710
<i>Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:20:44.710 --> 00:20:46.680
<i>There's something wrong with Silence Suzuka!</i>

00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:48.260
It's her left leg!

00:20:48.260 --> 00:20:50.310
Special Week-san!

00:20:48.980 --> 00:20:50.310
Trainer!

00:20:51.810 --> 00:20:53.350
That's not going to be good!

00:20:55.820 --> 00:20:57.940
<i>Suzuka-san! Suzuka-san!</i>

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:01.400
Suzuka!

00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:03.900
<i>Suzuka-san! Suzuka-san!</i>

00:21:05.580 --> 00:21:06.950
Suzuka-san!

00:21:07.820 --> 00:21:10.410
Don't let her put weight on her left leg!

00:21:10.410 --> 00:21:12.750
We need a medic immediately!

00:21:17.850 --> 00:21:19.420
Suzuka-san…

00:21:20.270 --> 00:21:21.410
Suzuka-san…

00:21:22.050 --> 00:21:23.250
It's okay.

00:21:23.250 --> 00:21:24.670
Don't worry.

00:21:25.390 --> 00:21:27.290
Trainer-san is here, too.

00:21:28.490 --> 00:21:33.310
You've always kept your
promises no matter what.

00:21:33.310 --> 00:21:34.350
So…

00:21:35.690 --> 00:21:39.830
I'm going to make you keep
your promise of running with me.

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:43.540
Suzuka-san, can you hear me?

00:21:43.540 --> 00:21:44.820
Suzuka-san!

00:21:47.810 --> 00:21:49.700
Thank you…

00:21:59.290 --> 00:22:00.640
Ow…

00:22:00.640 --> 00:22:02.580
You silly…

00:22:02.580 --> 00:22:04.170
I have…

00:22:05.610 --> 00:22:07.300
…to keep my promise.

00:22:09.550 --> 00:22:11.700
Yeah, this is just the beginning.

00:22:11.700 --> 00:22:12.890
Right, Spe?

00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:14.280
Yeah!

00:22:14.280 --> 00:22:17.020
We're going to run together!

00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:54.990
{\an8}Good luck!

00:23:55.305 --> 00:24:55.153
